With GRUB 2 on Debian and Ubuntu, I like to edit [[!format sh """/etc/default/grub"""]] and set [[!format sh """GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="""""]] or [[!format sh """GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="""""]]. I'm removing "quiet" and "splash" because I want to see all the boot messages.

Then run [[!format sh """sudo update-grub"""]] to make the change take effect in [[!format sh """/boot/grub/grub.cfg"""]].

